Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four (4) years.   Eighteen (18) months initial confinement, followed by thirty (30) months extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Repay $200.00 buy money; 
2) AODA assessment and follow through; 
3) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
4) Use only one doctor and only one pharmacist unless approved by agent; 
5) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
9) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.   
Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but is eligiible for the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is given 16 days credit.   
Minutes.
